Boy was taken to hospital after 'sleeper' prank went wrong in Manchester on Wednesday . 
  Greater Manchester Police have issued a warning to parents over the potentially fatal game . 
  The child is believed to have underlying health problems and is expected to make a full recovery . 
  The prank involves children holding their nose and mouth shut until they pass out . 
  Officers in Manchester believe it is a new craze and have alerted parents . 
 